items.name: Spider Woman Cosplay Outfit
items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras (Recommended for best quality, you may try other samplers)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 10

  • LORA weight for txt2img: reccomended 0.2-0.6.

  • Keys: wearing spiderwoman_cosplay_outfit, black and white outfit, red and blue outfit

Very easy to use, just use the keywords with the proper weights.

This model has good versatily with colors, it has been trained with suits of many different colors, that means you can type stuff like "red and white outfit" or almost any color combination to have the variation you want.

Some of the images are created with Controlnet poses packs, you can find them in my creator page.

It also works with anime, example in the posted images.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: Sawamura Haruka
items.description:
Child version

The child version of Haruka from both Yakuza Kiwami games.

It gets good quality results but needs some additional prompts to get accurate results, as by try to following the list seems to get a teenager version instead a child one.

See the prompts in the images to get a reference.

--------------------------------------------------

Young version

Haruka's version from Yakuza 3 and 4.

Made with just 19 images. The result is not pretty bad...but its needs some prompts for color correction.

The invocation is the same as the adult model, but instead add young after the name in curve brackets.

--------------------------------------------------

v2.0

This time the new version is made with a set of 35 images from Yakuza 5 and Yakuza 6, so it's a huge improve in quality and control over the character. It has very good results on photorealistic models like ChilloutMix.

Works best between 0.7~1, depending on the model.

The keywords are the same as the previous version.

--------------------------------------------------

v1.0

This is my first upload to the page.

I've seen a few LoRAS dedicated to Yakuza character but Haruka was nowhere to be found, so I've decided to made this one.

Pretty simple. Made with just 4 images from Yakuza 6 with Kohya Trainer with Google Colab using SD 1.5 as base. The results are not bad but there's no much place to customize her hair, appearing with ponytail even if you use different style prompts.

To invoke her is just her name and the series title (ryu ga gotoku, yakuza). To get her default style from the game just add these prompts:

  • red t-shirt, denim skirt, grey hoodie jacket, hoodie down, brown boots,

items.name: Christina Chong
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Christina Chong is a British actress of Chinese descent. She's known for many roles in TV shows and films, including Star Trek, Star Wars, Nightfall, Doctor Who and Black Mirror.

This is a 1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (chr1sch0ng:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, sexy star trek uniform, trousers, pale skin, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6, red lips".

Suggested LoRA Weight:

Anywhere between 0.4-1

0.4 tends to be a more conservative amount, singular load range

Inpainting

Does a decent job of inpainting, leave restore faces off as it removes everything this LoRA adds.

Future Improvements:

  • more training images, would like to get to the 100+ range

  • I would like to cover other parts of the body, but that may require a name change

  • simpler captions when training, "face covered" in prompts will occasionally get you an image of someone wearing a mask

I also have no idea why, but sometimes it will just generate a floating small planet?
All in all few problems that mainly come from the nature of her dataset.
I don't know if Sailor Moon datasets just suck or if it's me that sucks and I'm just to stupid to work with them sometimes lmao.

Let me know if you have any issues.

Used embeddings for sample pictures:

EasyNegative

bad_prompt_version2

If you have any feedback or questions just write in the comments or hit me up on reddit or discord.

items.name: Alfred Augustus Glendening style
items.description:
Alfred Augustus Glendening was an English landscape painter known for his depictions of idyllic rural scenes and picturesque landscapes. Active during the late 19th and early 20th centuries, Glendening's artwork captured the beauty and tranquility of the English countryside.

Glendening's paintings often feature rolling hills, meandering rivers, and peaceful countryside settings. He had a keen eye for capturing the nuances of light and atmospheric effects, infusing his landscapes with a sense of harmony and serenity. His skillful use of color and brushwork added depth and realism to his scenes, creating a sense of immersion for the viewer.

A significant aspect of Glendening's work was his ability to evoke a nostalgic sentiment, transporting viewers to a bygone era characterized by simpler times and a romanticized view of rural life. His landscapes often featured rural laborers, grazing livestock, and quaint cottages, evoking a sense of pastoral charm.

Glendening's paintings were highly sought after, and he gained recognition both in England and abroad. His artwork was frequently exhibited at prestigious venues, including the Royal Academy of Arts in London.

As a landscape painter, Alfred Augustus Glendening made a significant contribution to the Victorian and Edwardian art scene, capturing the essence of the English countryside in his idyllic and picturesque landscapes. His paintings continue to be admired for their evocative beauty, tranquil compositions, and ability to transport viewers to a simpler and more idyllic time.

items.name: Sword Armor&Wings——万剑魔甲
items.description:
5.6 update:

Use the revsoap28D_v11 large model to retrain a version, and the material itself has not been changed.

The effect: a little more realistic, but not by much.

Since normal results still cannot be obtained in other large models, it is still defined as: unusable

————————————————————————————————————————

An experimental training about AI painting, in order to explore the basic algorithm of AI painting.

If you are interested in the prototype, you can search for the Chinese name.

Based on the perfectWorld_v2Baked large model training, because I tried SD1.5, ChilloutMix, Anything V5 as the basic model, the result was even worse.

The base resolution is 512*1024.

Without any experience, I can only try a little bit according to the tutorial. The current conclusion is that AI cannot recognize things that are completely absent in its own database. Therefore, the learning process of AI painting cannot even conduct a detailed analysis of the training objects.

At present, it is completely impossible to see that AI painting has any deconstruction algorithm for human body or three-dimensional space.

For me, this model is almost unusable,because it is too limited,such as it can only be used for the basic resolution, the pose is single, even with the pose model, it is almost impossible to see, there is no model versatility, and so on.

Just ask someone to do better,if it arouses the interest of professionals,I hope to make a usable model, I would be very grateful.

5.6更新：

用revsoap28D_v11大模型重新训练一版，素材本身未作改动。

效果是：更写实了一点，但不多。

由于在其它大模型中依旧不能出正常结果，故依然定义为：不能用。

————————————————————————————————————————

关于AI绘画的一个实验性质的训练，为了探索AI绘画的基础算法。

如果对原型感兴趣，可以搜索中文名。

基于perfectWorld_v2Baked大模型训练，因为尝试过SD1.5、ChilloutMix、Anything V5做基础模型，结果更糟。

基础分辨率为512*1024。

没有任何经验，只能根据教程一点一点试，目前得出的结论是：AI是认不清自己数据库内完全没有的事物的，故AI绘画的学习过程甚至都做不到对训练对象的完全拆解。

目前也完全看不出AI绘画对人体，或者对立体空间有任何解构的算法。

此模型对我来说，几乎是不可用的，因为局限太大，比如只能用于基础分辨率，姿势单一，甚至加上openpose也几乎没法看，没有模型泛用性，等等。

只求抛砖引玉，如果引起了大神的兴趣，希望能做出可用的模型，不胜感激。

items.description:
Get early access to build and test build, be able to try all epochs and test them by yourself on Patreon or contact me for support on Discord

To support me you can buy me a coffe at https://ko-fi.com/antonioriolo

Install Instructions:

open stable diffusion -> extensions -> install from URL -> https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet.git

click Apply and restart UI

Then download from https://huggingface.co/webui/ControlNet-modules-safetensors/tree/main the file control_openpose-fp16.safetensor

place it inside extensions/sd-webui-controlnet/models

After all of this, you will have a ControlNet v1.1.112 just above Script in txt2image tab

Open it, place the pose you want to replicate by selecting it from your computer and place it in the image selection square box. You can also drag and drop.

Select preprocessor NONE, check Enable Checkbox, select control_openpose-fp16 in Model list, check Controlnet is more important in Control Mode.

Then generate your image, don't forget to write a proper prompt for the image.

I uploaded the pose images in sitting_controlnet folder and 1 example generated image with that pose on sitting_examples using the same prompt for all of them and my model betterCuteAsian. But you can modify the prompt to fit what you want.

Enjoy!

If you'd like to support my efforts and have access to early and bleeding edge builds, please think about joining my Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/betterCuteAsians

items.name: [ChumpyChoo] Toriel (Undertale) LoRA
items.description:
This is a custom LoRA model for the character Toriel from the popular video game Undertale. I trained the model using 179 high-quality images and utilized the AbyssOrangeMix3 model. I manually removed each watermark from each image used in the training, then upscaled the images for the highest possible quality.

For optimal results, I recommend using the Euler a sampler, with the following recommended parameters:

  • CFG scale of 7

  • 20 steps

  • hires upscaler set to Latent (nearest-exact)

  • 20 hires steps

  • Denoising strength of 0.52

For optimal performance, it is recommended that the weight of the LoRA be set within the range of 0.6-0.8.

To accurately depict Toriel's appearance, I suggest including furry, goat_girl, goat ears, furry female, and purple dress in the positive prompt. Additionally, if you want Toriel to have horns, simply place horns in the positive prompt.

Please feel free to leave a comment below if you have any requests for LoRA models.

items.name: Alice March
items.description:
📝Biography📝

(generation advice below) 👇

🌟Alice March 🌟

whose birth name is Patrice Auraura Marie Watson, is an American film actress born on February 13, 1994, in San Diego, California. She made her debut in the entertainment industry in 2012 at the age of 18 and is primarily known for her work in videos and web scenes.

Apart from working with film studios, Alice has also appeared in videos with various famous actresses such as Abella Danger, Chloe Foster, Dillion Harper, and Joseline Kelly. As of 2023, Alice March has a net worth of approximately $2 million USD, and her salary per video is estimated to be around $1450. Alice is also active on social media, with a significant presence on Instagram, where she posts pictures of her personal and professional life.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling (Using auto1111 or similar UX) 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted between 0.65 to 1.

  • Lower weighting needed often for headshots.

  • Samples done with CyberRealistic v20 with sampling steps above 20, generally between 40 to 80 using Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras and UniPC.

  • When testing a prompt, I often do a low lowres gen of multiple images, then choose the seed I like and upscale.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Portrait and close-ups work great using Hires. fix and 8X NMKD-Faces at 0.15 denoise strength.

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two, but often just the Hires. fix is good enough to capture enough details for the subject matter.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • The prompts continue to evolve. CyberRealistic is a reasonably flexible model for being realism focused and still capturing abstract concepts. I still think they have trumped the SD 1.5 game. 👑

  • Feedback appreciated. Please leave a review if you've used this LORA. 👍

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there.
